I thought barbell seal rows were named so because the Navy seals did them as part of their training, but watching my gymbro flop up and down on the bench strapped to 2 plates made me have a folk etymology clearpill moment and now I know it's because you literally look like a seal

The "Banshees of Inisherin" film probably has the first non-insufferable depiction of what would be called Nietzschean morality in normie cinema. A man sacrifices the everyday in the name of great art, his friend goes even further for their friendship, at the end they are equals.

It does carry the unmistakable stench of reddit but that's like complaining about a rancid smell at the fishmonger's store. Unless you are ready to turn into a forest hermit and abandon the century it's just the lower manifestation of the spirit of the age.

I guess, if we map by Zarathustra, it's the camel stage in suffering his friend's idle chatter year after year, the lion stage where he abandons him in the name of Mozart, eternal music, "I will" instead of "I shall", then at last the child of forgetfulness and "a new beginning".
Also the Irish foid character had a degree of forehead development that I, admittedly, found somewhat alluring.

At one point in the 60s the Pentagon directly financed a think tank dedicated to discrediting or misinterpreting Dr. Otto Warburg's work. The "sugar feeds cancer" concept was probably pretty straightforward invented by the US military. It's why they called it "the war on cancer".

The military grift, oncology grift, and the nuclear grift basically fully overlap and the same people switch from one field to the other completely free, which is why you get bizarre ideas like Warfarin or treating cancer with radiotherapy that obviously root in weapons research.
The "avant garde" concept already feels so outdated.

The idea of having a "national epic" is one of those concepts that could have only made sense in the 19th century. Similar to "nihilism" or psychoanalysis in the last. The conditions simply no longer exist to keep any of them coherent. Wonder what it will be for our current time.

I guess a lot of the stuff that comes to mind like neo-darwinism, "the brain is a computer", etc. is just plainly wrong instead of "not even wrong", but maybe we here have the benefit of looking at it from the fringes
